CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1782308901
OL,3,C'Health board failed our pregnant
OL,4,Cdaughter' says family after epilepsy
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FA family from Barry whose daughter
OL,8,Fdied during an epileptic seizure feels
OL,9,Fshe was 'let down' by a lack of
OL,10,Fspecialised care.
OL,12,FMegan Gardiner was 25 years old, and
OL,13,F17 weeks pregnant when she died from
OL,14,FSudden Unexpected Death in Epilepsy,
OL,15,For SUDEP.
OL,17,FIn an episode of Y Byd ar Bedwar, her
OL,18,Ffamily recall the tragic day they lost
OL,19,Ftheir daughter.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,451,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1782308901
OL,3,C'Health board failed our pregnant
OL,4,Cdaughter' says family after epilepsy
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,F"I went up to her room...and I could
OL,8,Fsee Megan's foot poking out of the
OL,9,Fquilt," says Alison, Megan's mother.
OL,11,F"She'd fallen in between the wall and
OL,12,Fthe bed. I pulled her out, but it was
OL,13,Freally clear that she'd already died."
OL,15,F"That image will haunt me for the rest
OL,16,Fof my life," Alison says.
OL,18,FMegan's younger sister, Tesni,
OL,19,Fremembers the moment she was told the
OL,20,Fnews.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@GO]sD@AOUuD@fO]wD@AOUxD@LO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,451,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1782308901
OL,3,C'Health board failed our pregnant
OL,4,Cdaughter' says family after epilepsy
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,F"I just said, 'no, that's not
OL,8,Ftrue...how could this happen to our
OL,9,Ffamily?"
OL,11,FMegan was diagnosed with a severe form
OL,12,Fof epilepsy at the age of 13.
OL,13,FAccording to her mother, Alison, her
OL,14,Fseizures were unpredictable and could
OL,15,Fhappen "up to three times a week".
OL,17,FIn 2022, Megan became pregnant and was
OL,18,Fadvised to reduce the dosage of one of
OL,19,Fher medications twice to protect the
OL,20,Fhealth of her unborn baby, which she
OL,21,Fconsented to.
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@HOUwD@aO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,451,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1782308901
OL,3,C'Health board failed our pregnant
OL,4,Cdaughter' says family after epilepsy
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FHowever, Alison claims that
OL,8,Fspecialists at Cardiff and Vale
OL,9,FUniversity Health Board failed to
OL,10,Fexplain that lowering the medication
OL,11,Fcould increase the frequency of
OL,12,FMegan's seizures and, consequently,
OL,13,Fher risk of SUDEP.
OL,15,FSUDEP is the sudden, unexpected death
OL,16,Fof someone with epilepsy, who was
OL,17,Fotherwise healthy. In SUDEP cases, no
OL,18,Fother cause of death is found when an
OL,19,Fautopsy is done.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,451,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1782308901
OL,3,C'Health board failed our pregnant
OL,4,Cdaughter' says family after epilepsy
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FAccording to Epilepsy Action, more
OL,8,Fthan 1 in 1,000 people with epilepsy
OL,9,Fdie from SUDEP every year, but for
OL,10,Fthose with severe epilepsy like Megan,
OL,11,Fthat number increases to 1 in every
OL,12,F100.
OL,14,FThe family believes that had Megan
OL,15,Fknown about her individual risk of
OL,16,FSUDEP, she may not have consented to
OL,17,Fthe change in her medication.
OL,19,F"She has been failed" Tesni says.
OL,26,@{D@AOU{D@UO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
